    "updated_at": "2014-02-28T23:17:18Z",
    "body": "A sneaky/hacky way to get around this would be to assign a `AbortingWriter` as a task-local output handle. When the task exits (via fail) this aborting writer could abort the process on exit (if it had anything written to it).\n",
