    "created_at": "2014-03-01T00:12:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-03-01T00:12:25Z",
    "body": "I think that fail behavior needs to be more configurable in general, though I'm not sure how much should be dynamic and how much should be static. One of the things mentioned in the [EASTL docs](http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2007/n2271.html) is that game engines sometimes avoid the `assert` function because its behavior can't be overridden.\n",
